The pickle with assuming the options are universal is that different editors have different ways of configuring the same property. For example, enabling/disabling line numbers in CodeMirror is done by setting the `lineNumbers` property to `true` or `false`. In Monaco, this is done by setting a `lineNumbers` property [an enum value](https://microsoft.github.io/monaco-editor/api/modules/monaco.editor.html#linenumberstype).

My intention behind making the bindings specific to CodeMirror was to allow users to configure options for each editor specifically. For example:

```json
{
  "codeMirror": {
    "lineNumbers": true
  },
  "monaco": {
    "lineNumbers": "relative"
  }
}
```

Depending on the editor that the user has selected in their environment, a different configuration object would be passed down and each editor would support the configuration depending on its internal logic.

