Specifically "code" and "message" at the root of an error object have confused users, and the Redfish spec recommends clients ignoring this. This is because the `@Message.ExtendedInfo` property is expected to contain every message necessary for the client to consume.

I recommend structuring the "message_detail" dictionary like this to ease of use:

```
messages_detail = {
    "Status": response.status,
    "Successful": true/false,
    "Messages": [ <copy of the contents of @Message.ExtendedInfo ]
}
```

We could also have a fallback where if `@Message.ExtendedInfo` is not present, we can form the object like this:

```
messages_detail = {
    "Status": response.status,
    "Successful": true/false,
    "Messages": [
        { "MessageId": response.dict["error"]["code"], "Message": response.dict["error"]["message"] }
    ]
}
```

