In the code above we have
```c++
    OT_TOOL_PACKED_BEGIN
    struct Keys
    {
        Mle::Key mMleKey;
        Mac::Key mMacKey;
    } OT_TOOL_PACKED_END;

    union HashKeys
    {
        Crypto::HmacSha256::Hash mHash;
        Keys                     mKeys;
    };
```

How about changing the `Keys` type to use `otMacKey` (which is the literal key) instead of the union types `Mac:Key`? (it may also help to actually define a `Mac::LiteralKey` type as mirror of `otMacKey` (with `Clear()` and other helper methods) which we use here).
